1 olive oil
1 tin tinned cherry tomatoes
1 packet diced bacon
2 clove garlic
1 bag herbs
1 packet tomato paste
1 tsp brown sugar
1 tsp white wine vinegar
20 head butter
1 packet Onion Chutney
2 eggs
2 Butter Burger Buns
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet mayonnaise
1 pinch Chili Flakes

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Drain cherry tomatoes and place on a lined
oven tray with a pinch of salt and pepper and a
drizzle of olive oil. Toss to coat.
• Roast until tomatoes are blistered,
8-12 minutes.

• While the cherry tomatoes are roasting, finely
chop garlic. Pick and roughly chop herb leaves.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium heat. Cook diced bacon, breaking
up with a spoon, until just golden 4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic, a pinch of chilli flakes (if using),
tomato paste and herbs, stirring, until fragrant,
1 minute.
• Add the brown sugar, white wine vinegar and
the butter. Stir to combine, 1 minute.
• Remove from heat. Stir through onion chutney
and season to taste.
• Transfer to a bowl and season to taste.

• Wipe out pan and return to medium-high heat
with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Fry eggs until egg whites are cooked and the
yolks are just firm, 4-5 minutes.

• While the eggs are frying, slice burger buns in
half and place on a second oven tray. Sprinkle
bases with shredded Cheddar cheese.
• Bake until heated through and cheese is melted,
2-4 minutes.

• Build your burger by spooning bacon jam over
base, then top with roast cherry tomatoes, fried
egg and salad leaves.
• Spread mayonnaise over the top burger bun
and serve. Enjoy!